text: Joseph J. Went (born September 16, 1930) is a retired United States Marine Corps four-star general. His final job was as Assistant Commandant of the Marine Corps and Chief of Staff. He retired in 1990 after 38 years of service. ==References== Category:1930 births Category:Living people Category:American generals Category:American military personnel of the Vietnam War Category:Military people from Connecticut
